<body>
    <h1>2) Kubernetes</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 class=3D"readme file file-markup wiki-content" id=3D"id-2)Kuber=
netes-KubernetesControlPlane:">Kubernetes Control Plane:</h2>
<p class=3D"readme file file-markup wiki-content">It consists of multiple c=
omponents that controls and makes the whole cluster function:</p>
<div class=3D"readme file file-markup wiki-content">
<ul>
<li>API Server which communicate with and perform operations on the Kuberne=
tes cluster,</li>
<li>Scheduler responsible for assigning a worker node to each deployable co=
mponent,</li>
<li>Controller Manager performs cluster-level functions such as replicating=
 components, keeping track of worker nodes, etc.,</li>
<li>etcd, a reliable distributed data store that stores the whole cluster c=
onfiguration persistently.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h2 class=3D"fileview" id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Workernodes">Worker nodes</h2>
<p class=3D"fileview">Machines that actually run our containerized applicat=
ions</p>
<div class=3D"fileview">
<ul>
<li>Docker container runtime, which runs your containers,</li>
<li>Kubelet which talks to the master and controls containers on the node,<=
/li>
<li>Kube-Proxy which proxies and load balances network traffic between your=
 application components.<br><br></li>
</ul>
</div>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image confluence-external-resource" alt=3D"Alt text" src=3D"http=
s://bytebucket.org/wymarsalis/paas/raw/c29f8b9184a1f9781e521e5fd63c3e801144=
