=3Da2ecf604e6d8597e98f8adf3d0cddebddeb8aeb7" data-image-src=3D"https://byte=
bucket.org/wymarsalis/paas/raw/c29f8b9184a1f9781e521e5fd63c3e801144133c/tra=
ining/Screenshot_from_2017-11-08_22-53-18.png?raw=3Dtrue&amp;token=3Da2ecf6=
04e6d8597e98f8adf3d0cddebddeb8aeb7"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Kubernetescomposants">Kubernetes composants</h2>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Node">Node</h4>
<p>A nodeis a worker machine in Kubernetes.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/nodes/"=
 class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/docs/concep=
ts/architecture/nodes/</a></p>
<h4 class=3D"readme file file-markup wiki-content" id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Po=
d">Pod</h4>
<p>Group of one or more containers, with shared storage/network, and a spec=
ification for how to run the containers.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod/"=
 class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/docs/concep=
ts/workloads/pods/pod/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-ReplicaSet">ReplicaSet</h4>
<p>Configuration object used during deployment in order to set the number o=
f pods replicas wanted.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controller=
s/replicaset/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.=
io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/replicaset/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Deployment">Deployment</h4>
<p>Configuration describing the state wanted for Pods and ReplicaSet.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controller=
s/deployment/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.=
io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Namespace">Namespace</h4>
<p>Namespaces are intended for use in environments with many users spread a=
cross multiple teams, or projects.</p>
<p>Namespaces are a way to divide cluster resources between multiple users/=
env (dev/int/prod).</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-wit=
h-objects/namespaces/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kub=
ernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/namespaces/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Service">Service</h4>
<p>Service is an abstraction that make possible to access multiple Pods by =
node Port, VIp or public Ip.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/=
service/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/do=
cs/concepts/services-networking/service/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Ingress">Ingress</h4>
<p>An API object that manages external access to the services in a cluster,=
 typically HTTP.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/=
ingress/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/do=
cs/concepts/services-networking/ingress/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-ResourceQuota">ResourceQuota</h4>
<p>Resource quotas are a tool for administrators to define quota in namespa=
ce.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/policy/resource-quot=
as/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/docs/co=
ncepts/policy/resource-quotas/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-Role/ClusterRole">Role/ClusterRole</h4>
<p>A ClusterRole can be used to grant the permissions as a Role</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/=
rbac/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/docs/=
reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-2)Kubernetes-RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding">RoleBinding/Clust=
erRoleBinding</h4>
<p>A role binding grants the permissions defined in a role to a user or set=
 of users.</p>
<p>Doc: <a href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/=
rbac/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/docs/=
reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/</a></p>
